President Trump signed the largest economic relief package in American history, worth $2.2 trillion, to provide urgent relief to families, workers, and businesses affected by the COVID-19 pandemic. The package includes direct payments to individuals and support for small businesses. Trump also mentioned the progress being made in manufacturing ventilators and other medical supplies, as well as the communication and information-sharing with other countries like China. Various members of Trump's administration and Congress expressed their gratitude for the bipartisan effort in passing the relief package and highlighted the importance of protecting American workers and businesses. Trump expressed optimism for a strong economic rebound in the future.